Package com.pionix.controllers

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IDbController<T>
    Interface for DbControllers A DbController should have basic operations like get, delete, update, create, size, listing This is the interface for them
    IDbSet<T>
    A DbSet is like a table in SQL It should hold some kind of model It should have basic operations like get, push, delete, length This interface is for future DbSets
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AdministratorController
    AdministratorController is the DbController for the Administrator Model
    BranchController
    BranchController is the DbController for the Branch data model
    BranchEmployeeController
    BranchEmployeeController is the DbController for the BranchEmployee data model
    CustomerController
    CustomerController is the DbController for the Customer data model
    DbArray<T>
    Custom dynamic array implementation for IDbSet It can dynamically add and remove items Stored as Array
    DbArrayList<T>
    ArrayList container implementation for IDbSet Stored as ArrayList
    DbController<T>
    DbController is the base Controller for any data type Construct objects from models and store them in Database It has basic operations for any possible Entity like get, delete, create update operations It stores the data as IDbSet implemented as DbArrayList It both controls and stores the data set like a Database table.
    ShipmentController
    ShipmentController is the DbController for the Shipment data model
    TransportationPersonnelController
    TransportationPersonnelController is the DbController for the TransportationPersonnel data model
    UserController<T extends User>
    Base controller for available users of the system Every user has a username, so we have this basic operations like get and delete For creation it is different with every user Customer can be created with just a name But BranchEmployee can't, it needs also an available branch This controller creates new tables for given type value
